column2: Estadi Ciutat de València (in Spanish Estadio Ciudad de Valencia, City of Valencia Stadium in English) is a football stadium in Valencia and is the home ground of Levante UD. The stadium holds 25,354 and was built in 1969
The Iberostar Stadium is a football stadium located in Palma, Balearic Islands, Spain
Campos de Sport de El Sardinero ($022El Sardinero Sport Fields$022), is a multi-purpose stadium in Santander, Spain
The Stadio delle Alpi was a football and athletics stadium in Turin, Italy and was the home of both Juventus Football Club and Torino Football Club between 1990 and 2006
Juventus Stadium is an all-seater association football stadium in the Vallette borough of Turin, Italy, and the home of Serie A club Juventus Football Club
Stadio Armando Picchi is a multi-purpose stadium in Livorno, Italy
Stadio Carlo Castellani is a multi-purpose stadium in Empoli, Italy
Stadio Mario Rigamonti is a football ground in Brescia, Italy, home of Brescia Calcio
Stadio Moretti was a multi-use stadium in Udine, Italy
Estadio San Mamés, AKA La Catedral (The Cathedral), is a football stadium in Bilbao, Basque Country, Spain
Anoeta is a multi-purpose stadium in Donostia-San Sebastián, Spain
Stadio San Paolo is a multi-purpose stadium in the western suburb of Fuorigrotta in Naples, Italy, and is the third largest football stadium in Italy after the San Siro and Stadio Olimpico
Stadio Ennio Tardini, commonly referred to as just Il Tardini, is a football stadium in Parma, Italy, located near the centre of Parma, between the town centre and the city walls
Stadio Angelo Massimino (previously known as Stadio Cibali) is a multi-use stadium in Catania, Italy
Campo de Fútbol de Vallecas previously known as Estadio Teresa Rivero is a multi-use stadium in Madrid, Spain
Estadio Municipal de Riazor is a multi-purpose stadium in A Coruña, Galicia, Spain
Stadio Via del Mare is a multi-purpose stadium in Lecce, Italy
Stadio Filadelfia was a multi-use stadium in Turin, Italy
Estadio La Rosaleda (literally The Rose Garden) is a football stadium in the city of Málaga, in Andalusia, southern Spain
Mediterráneo Stadium is a multi-purpose stadium in Almería, Spain
Stadio Friuli is a multi-purpose stadium in Udine, Italy
Stadio Renzo Barbera (previously and still commonly known as Stadio La Favorita) is a football stadium in Palermo, Italy
The Stadio San Nicola is a multi-use all-seater stadium designed by Renzo Piano in Bari, Italy
Nou Estadi is a multi-purpose stadium in Tarragona, Catalonia, Spain
San Mames Barria (Spanish: Nuevo San Mamés, English: New San Mames) is the name of the Athletic Bilbao's new football stadium, which is under construction
The Vicente Calderón Stadium is the home stadium of La Liga football club Atlético Madrid and is located in the Arganzuela district of Spanish capital Madrid
Estadi Cornellà-El Prat (Catalan pronunciation: [əsˈtaði kurnəˈʎa əɫ ˈpɾat]) is an all-seater football stadium on the outskirts of Cornellà and El Prat de Llobregat, near Barcelona (Catalonia, Spain)
Atleti Azzurri d'Italia is a stadium in Bergamo, Italy, used by the Atalanta and Albinoleffe football teams
Estadio Municipal de Ipurua is a multi-use stadium in Eibar, Spain
The Stadio Oreste Granillo is a football stadium in Reggio Calabria, Italy
Estadi de Sarrià (Catalan pronunciation: [əsˈtaði ðə səriˈa]) was a football stadium in Barcelona, Catalonia, Spain
Stadio Dino Manuzzi is a football stadium in Cesena, Italy

Stadio Olimpico di Torino (originally Stadio Benito Mussolini and formally Stadio Comunale Vittorio Pozzo) is a stadium located in the Santa Rita district in the south of Turin, Italy that is the home of Serie B club Torino
Stadio Marc'Antonio Bentegodi is a stadium in Verona, Italy
Stadio Renato Dall'Ara is a multi-purpose stadium in Bologna, Italy
Estadio de La Romareda is the home stadium of Real Zaragoza, in Zaragoza
Estadio El Molinón is an association football stadium in Gijón, Asturias-Spain
Estadio José Rico Pérez is a multi-purpose stadium in Alicante, Spain
Camp Nou (Catalan pronunciation: [kamˈnɔw], New Field) is a football stadium in Barcelona, Catalonia, Spain which has been the home of Futbol Club Barcelona since 1957
Estadio Ramón Sánchez Pizjuán is a stadium in Seville, Spain
Estadio El Madrigal is a multi-purpose stadium in Vila-real, Spain, used since 1923
Stadio Artemio Franchi is a multi-purpose stadium in Siena, Italy
Stadio Adriatico - Giovanni Cornacchia is a stadium in Pescara, Abruzzo, Italy, which opened in 1955 and designed by Italian architect Luigi Piccinato
Stadio Città del Tricolore is a multi-purpose stadium in Reggio Emilia, Italy
Stadio Cino e Lillo Del Duca is a multi-purpose stadium in Ascoli Piceno, Italy
Stadio Artemio Franchi is a football stadium in Florence, Italy
Stadio Comunale Luigi Ferraris, also known as the Marassi from the name of the ward where the Marassi is located, is a multi-use stadium in Genoa, Italy
The Estadio Municipal de Balaídos (Spanish pronunciation: [balaˈiðos], $022Balaídos Municipal Stadium$022) is an all-seater football stadium in Vigo, Spain
The Estadio Santiago Bernabéu (Spanish pronunciation: [esˈtaðjo sanˈtjaɣo βernaˈβeu]) is an all-seater football stadium in Madrid, Spain
Estadio Coliseum Alfonso Pérez is a football stadium in Getafe, Spain
Estadio Mestalla is a football stadium in Valencia, Spain
The Estadio Benito Villamarín is a football stadium in Seville, Spain
The Stadio Giuseppe Meazza, also known as the San Siro, is a football stadium in Milan, Italy, located at geographical coordinates
Estadio El Sadar (between 2005-2011, known as Reyno de Navarra) is a football stadium in Pamplona, Navarre, Spain
Estadio José Zorrilla is a football stadium in Valladolid, Spain
Estadio Nuevo Los Cármenes is a multi-use stadium in Granada, Spain
Stadio Comunale $022Is Arenas$022 is a sports stadium in Quartu Sant'Elena, Sardinia, Italy
